{
  "stem": "7781.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First, Saturday, the most-- best day was Friday night, where the whole family used to gather around the table, and there was a festive meal, and-- and the candles, and the kiddush used to make the wine.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And was-- the light was bright and was very, very heartwarming, where looking back, it sort of was-- every Friday was a gathering of the family.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And no business, no nothing, and it was-- and left good memories.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, food that we could not eat the whole week, but on Friday we had food like chicken soup, and fish, and all kind of stuff that usually you did not get during the weekday.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My part?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My part was going with my mother to the market and help her carry the-- the basket with food.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't have no refrigeration, so everything had to be bought fresh.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I helped to carry the basket, whatever she would-- chicken, you know, live chicken and live fish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then she had to go to the guy-- to the shokhet, and-- and the chicken had to be killed, you know, according to the-- it was prescribed by Jewish law, and then was the fish, and you prepared-- she worked the whole day.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Just prepare the Friday and Shabbat meal, because Shabbat-- we didn't cook on Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she had-- she had some job on her hand to feed nine people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For two days.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yom-- Yom Kippur was a special, a solemn day.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was kind of hard on a kid, you know, because we couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When I grew up, you had to fast, and you couldn't-- you-- you had a hard time, you know, waiting until you got to eat again.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but and then after the-- the services, the whole family got together.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
